Ask HN: Any recommendations for full-service web dev vendors?
text:
I have some tech experience and a product idea that I think is economically viable. I don’t want to build/run it myself though. My ideal scenario is to hire a company that would handle all design/tech, both in the building stages and on-going maintenance, on-call, everything. Basically paying the company to be my dev team. It would be a relatively simple web application along with auth, payment, etc.

Is this realistic? Are there such companies you know of or have worked with? Toptal? Others? What is pricing like?

Much appreciated!

Ask HN: PayPal 2-factor utterly broken?
text:
Is it just me?

I just lost our paypal account for my company just by deleting an old phone number in the settings and adding a new one. After logging out there is no way to log back in, they refer me to their hotline.

A similar thing happened years ago when they introduced 2-factor, I never got that account back since I simply couldn't get through on their hotline. I had a private account with an old number, they introduced 2-factor and I missed their emails about it, and when I tried to login later, I was basically locked out.

Honestly we don't need Paypal in my company. So I guess I will heavily advocate against it in any companies I own or work in going forward.

Does lower cost of living due to automation compensate for jobs lost?
text:
For example, I'm a construction worker building houses. Then let's say a technology completely replaces my job because it's 10x less expensive than hiring me. I've lost my job. However, as companies compete using that technology to build houses more and more efficiently, the cost of housing would theoretically go down.

So my questions are:

1.Does automation actually reduce cost of living? (in an economy where competition is allowed)

2.Is the cost of living reduced enough to compensate for the people losing their jobs?

3.How much does the PACE of automation play a factor relative to other possible factors?

Interested to find any economic theories or concepts pertaining to this, whether relating to present day, or future.
